            <pb n="3" facs="#f0001"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#k">Cactuses.</hi>
                </head>
                <p>&#x2014;When one has been accustomed to see cac-<lb break="no"/>tuses only in our hothouses, one is astonished at the de-<lb break="no"/>gree of density and hardness which the ligneous fibres at-<lb break="no"/>tain in old cactus stems. The Indians know that cactus<lb break="yes"/>wood is incorruptible, and excellent for oars and for the<lb break="yes"/>thresholds of doors. There is hardly anything in vegetable<lb break="yes"/>physiognomy which makes so singular and ineffaceable an<lb break="yes"/>impression on a newly arrived person, as the sight of an<lb break="yes"/>arid plain thickly covered, like those near Cumana, New<lb break="yes"/>Barcelona, and Coro, and in the province of Jaen de Bra-<lb break="no"/>camoros, with columnar and candelabra-like divided cactus<lb break="yes"/>stems.&#x2014;<hi rendition="#i">Humboldt.</hi>
                </p>
            </div>
